  "abstract": "Sorghum (Sorghum bicolor) is known to be relat ively more tolerant to sal ini ty than other crops, such as maize\r\n(Zea mays) or legumes and thus has the potent ial to\r\nreplace maize in saline soils ( Igar tua et al . 1994). The\r\nexistence of large interspeci f ic (Yang et al . 1990) and\r\nint ra-speci f ic (Maas 1985, Azhar and McNe i l l y 1988,\r\nDe La Rosa-Ibarra and Mai t i 1995) var iat ion for sal ini ty\r\ntolerance of fers a scope for integrat ing these tolerant\r\ncrop genotypes wi th appropriate management practices\r\nto better exploi t the saline soils.",
